'''Nationwide Fountain''' is a fountain designed by sculptor Jim Ponter and architect Don Olson in downtown [[Columbus, Ohio]], United States. The abstract fountain features stacked geometric blocks of stone and [[bronze sculpture]]s of various animals, including a frog, lizard, and salmon.<ref name="SI">{{cite web |title=Nationwide Fountain, (sculpture). |url=https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!324715~!0#focus |publisher=[[Smithsonian Institution]] |accessdate=November 4, 2018}}</ref><ref name="OOSI">{{cite web |title=Nationwide Fountain |url=http://oosi.sculpturecenter.org/items/show/776 |website=Ohio Outdoor Sculpture Inventory |accessdate=November 4, 2018}}</ref>
The fountain was surveyed by the [[Smithsonian Institution]]'s "[[Save Outdoor Sculpture!]]" program in 1994.<ref name=SI/>
